      "type": "text",
      "description": "Photosynthesis is a process used by plants to convert light energy into chemical energy."
    },
    {
      "id": "point1",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "It occurs in chloroplasts within plant cells where chlorophyll captures sunlight."
    },
    {
      "id": "point2",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Water and carbon dioxide are the raw materials needed for photosynthesis, producing glucose and oxygen as products. "
    },
    {
      "id": "point3",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "This process is vital for plants' growth and also benefits other forms of life by providing them with energy and releasing oxygen into the atmosphere."
    }
